Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.380
 Buttonholes and Buttons 

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:12.440
 Select the "Buttonholes" menu 

00:00:14.800 --> 00:00:17.940
 Select the buttonhole n.51 

00:00:22.660 --> 00:00:25.980
 Select the icon "i 

00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:39.900
 Increase the distance of the buttonhole beams to 0.8 

00:00:47.100 --> 00:00:50.560
 Select the Buttonhole Length Measurement System 

00:00:53.800 --> 00:00:55.800
 Place the button against the display 

00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:07.320
 Use the multifunction knobs to determine the size of the button 

00:01:15.740 --> 00:01:17.740
 The program automatically adds 2 mm to compensate for the thickness of the button 

00:01:24.580 --> 00:01:28.180
 Use the 3A slide slotted foot 

00:01:32.420 --> 00:01:41.460
 The buttonhole is programmed and can be sewn without interruption 

00:01:59.460 --> 00:02:01.460
 Cut the threads automatically 

00:02:10.920 --> 00:02:16.920
 The same slot can be repeated as many times as desired 

00:02:48.860 --> 00:02:51.720
 Buttonholes can be saved in the "Personal Program" 

00:03:07.780 --> 00:03:09.780
 Attach the Buttons 

00:03:14.520 --> 00:03:16.520
 Return to the Slots menu 

00:03:20.120 --> 00:03:22.900
 Select the button sewing program n.60 

00:03:27.620 --> 00:03:29.620
 Use foot # 18 (optional) 

00:03:35.260 --> 00:03:38.260
 Place the button in its position on the fabric and under the foot 

00:03:44.680 --> 00:03:48.380
 Sew a few starting stitches and stop before the needle enters the right hole 

00:03:50.280 --> 00:03:56.780
 Use the handwheel to check the correct position and centering of the holes in the button 

00:03:59.120 --> 00:04:01.620
 Adjust the stitch width if necessary 

00:04:03.780 --> 00:04:05.780
 End the button sewing program 

00:04:13.580 --> 00:04:16.780
 Cut the threads automatically 

00:04:31.360 --> 00:04:34.640
 Tip: you can also use foot no. 20 C 

